                    Gucci's New Guy, the Return of the J. C. Penney Catalog and Alexander Wang's Bean Baggage                
Plus, Rick Owens’s ballsy runway move, Obama’s right to shoes and more from the week in style.
By HILARY MOSS
















Business Briefing

                    Macy’s and J.C. Penney to Close Stores                
Macy’s said that it would close 14 stores but also open two new locations, while J. C. Penney said that it would close about 40 stores this year.










Business Briefing

                    Shares of J.C. Penney Jump on Holiday Sales Report                
The retailer said same-store sales rose 3.7 percent in November and December, offering a glimpse of what was expected to be a strong holiday season for retailers.











                    J.C. Penney and Macy’s Post Lackluster Sales Before Holidays                 
Sales were tepid at both chains, causing executives to wonder when improvements in the economy and employment would become palpable in their stores.
By RACHEL ABRAMS and HIROKO TABUCHI














                    J.C. Penney Reports Flat Sales                
Consumer spending continues to hurt the retailer, whose net sales were below analysts’ expectations.











                    J.C. Penney Names Home Depot Executive as Its Next Chief                
The company, tapping a seasoned retail hand, said Marvin Ellison would become president in November and chief executive next August.
By HIROKO TABUCHI














                    Return to Traditions Spurs Optimism at J. C. Penney                
The retailer, which just two years ago appeared to be teetering on the brink of collapse, says it is now back on sound footing.











                    Walmart, J.C. Penney and Other Retailers See a Tentative Shopper                
Walmart’s domestic sales were flat instead of falling, Penney’s sharply cut its losses, and Kohl’s sales and profit fell. Macy’s gave a forecast that will hinge on customer sentiment.
By ELIZABETH A. HARRIS













Advertising

                    J.C. Penney Burnishes Its Liz Claiborne Brand                
After some years of zigzagging in promoting Claiborne, Penney’s wants to project it as a multigenerational brand, aiming for 35-year-old women as well as longtime fans.
By STUART ELLIOTT













Business Briefing

                    J. C. Penney Files Appeal in Macy’s Contract Case                
The company appealed a New York state court ruling that found it had interfered with a contract between Macy’s and Martha Stewart Living Omnimedia by selling the celebrity’s home goods.











                    Ruling Against J.C. Penney in Dispute With Macy’s Over Martha Stewart Products                
The ruling that J.C. Penney unlawfully interfered with a merchandising agreement may be the penultimate chapter of a long-running dispute among three famous names in retailing.
By HILARY STOUT












